national_caveats:
Data not available between 1991 - 2000;
A revised national surveillance case defnition for Influenza was implemented on 29 October 2008
A revised national surveillance case definition for Meningococcal invasive was implemented on 1 July 2010
Hepatitis C unspecified included incident hepatitis C from all jurisdictions between 1991 - 2008 and from NT and Qld between 1993 to present
Hepatitis (NEC) included reports of Hepatitis D and Hepatitis E between 1991 - 1998
A revised national surveillance case definition for Murray Valley encephalitis virus infecticn was implemented on 1 July 2010
A revised national surveiliance case definition for Japanese encephalitis was implemented on 1 July 2010

A revised national surveillance case definition for Kunjin virus infection was implemented on 1 July 2010;
Disease reported as Murray Valley Encephalitis between 2001 - 2008

Data not available between 1991 - 2008;
Data from Jan 1991 to Dec 2000 included notifications of Japanese encephalitis, Kunjin and Murray Valley Encephalitis from 2001, these diseases were notified separately from most jurisdictions
A revised national surveiliance case definition for Brucellosis was in effect on 1 July 2010
A revised national surveillance case definition for Tularaemia was implemented on 29 October 2008
